name: Whole Wheat Peanut Butter Banana Bread
author: joshllorio
summary: This is our version of wheat banana bread. As its name suggests, it's even more tasty than the original.
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Beat bananas, honey, oil, eggs, peanut butter, and vanilla extract in a bowl until smooth
Combine pastry flour, bread flour, wheat germ, salt, and baking soda in a large bowl; make a well in the flour mixture
Pour banana mixture into well and stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients until batter is just moistened
Pour batter into prepared loaf pan
Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 1 hour
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes before removing to cool completely on a wire rack
